                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18010916-96-victim663 t18010916-96-viclabel501"></join>; I keep <placeName id="t18010916-96-crimeloc502">the Jolly Sailor, in Back-lane, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18010916-96-crimeloc502" type="placeName" value="the Jolly Sailor, in Back-lane, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18010916-96-crimeloc502" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18010916-96-off499 t18010916-96-crimeloc502"></join>: On Tuesday evening, the 7th of July, about half past six o'clock, the prisoner, in company with another woman, came into my house; I saw the prisoner take a quart pewter pot off the tap-room table, and wrap it up in her apron, then she sat down and called for a pint of beer, she drank the beer and paid me for it; I let her go out of doors, and then I followed and asked her what she had got; she said, nothing; I unwrapped her apron and found the quart pot; Rodgers has it; I am sure it is my pot, I saw her take it.(Edward Rodgers, the Officer, produced the pot, which was deposed to by Newton.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I went in for a pint of beer and asked him leave to take a pot to measure some gooseberries, and I understood that he gave me leave. <rs id="t18010916-96-verdict503" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18010916-96-verdict503" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 37.</p>
